title: Dictionary of Literary Biography - Nobel Prize Laureates in Lite
description:
Published/Released: August 2007
Original Copyright: 2007
ISBN 13: 9781414428635
ISBN 10: 1414428634
Format: PDF
Pages: ~2500

Volumes 329-332 (I-IV) of this acclaimed series are devoted to coverage of Nobel Prize Laureates. These volumes explore in detail the lives and careers of some of the most notable names in literature, including Samuel Beckett, Saul Bellow, Pearl S. Buck, T. S. Eliot, William Faulkner, Nadine Gordimer, Hermann Hesse, Yasunari Kawabata, Sinclair Lewis, Toni Morrison, Pablo Neruda, Bertrand Russell, Nelly Sachs, John Steinbeck and many others.

In addition, many entries include presentation speeches from the Swedish Academy, banquet speeches by the recipients, autobiographical statements and press releases.
